          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                                        <date>Jany 18, 1849</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Isaac Leeser Eq </addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Revd &amp; dear Sir</p>
                              <p>For some days past I have been<lb/> very unwell The cholera
                                        attacked<lb/> me very hard but thanks to a Divine<lb/>
                                        Providence I am again restor'd<lb/> to Health &amp; at your
                                        Service<lb/> I instructed my Book Keeper<lb/> to answer your
                                        Last Letter, which<lb/> he informs me he did. I must
                                        here<lb/> confirm his words, vz, some of those<lb/> Books
                                        are not only Insured but<lb/> appear to have been used.</p>
                              <p>Its strange not one of the members<lb/> of the Portuguese
                                        Congregation<lb/> seem willing to buy any of your<lb/>
                                        <sic>Preyer</sic> Books. now I presume<lb/> If there was
                                        none here they would<lb/> be forwarding their Orders to
                                        you<lb/> or elsewhere for various Books<lb/> yet here they
                                        are &amp; not a soul<lb/> needs them. I am happy to
                                        inform<lb/> you the <add>?</add>etcher Books are moving<lb/>
                                        I sent <persName>Emanuel Mobile</persName> 1 Doz Four<lb/>
                                        of each price &amp; have left 7 c2.75—11 c 2 50</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>&amp; 4 c $3.00—these Books will sell<lb/> here all the year round.
                                        I see them<lb/> at your Invoice price</p>
                              <p>I was notified by <persName>Barnett</persName>
                                        <add>?</add><lb/> &amp; a <persName>De Young</persName> (not
                                        positive of the latter)<lb/> that the <date>December</date>
                                        No of the<lb/> Occident did not reach them<lb/> but the
                                                  <date>January</date> Number<lb/> is at hand &amp;
                                        I have waited<lb/> on the two first Gentlemen &amp;<lb/>
                                        find they are in receipt of their<lb/> number for this
                                        present<lb/> month.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I beg to return you<lb/> for my most Sincere
                                        thanks<lb/> for your notice of our Loan<lb/> on Whole
                                        Congregation will feel<lb/> themselves your Debtors. The
                                                  <persName>Revd Mr Carrolina</persName> has
                                        now<lb/> been here some time endeavouring<lb/> to obtain the
                                        office of Reader to<lb/> the Portuguese Congregation<lb/> It
                                        is still expected <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> will<lb/>
                                        come but should he decline<lb/> the <persName>Revd
                                                  Carrolina</persName> will not
                                        <sic>suceed</sic><lb/> He is very unpopular—</p>
                              <p>I have given to <persName>Joseph Turner</persName><lb/> the Numbers
                                        1c10 of this Volume<lb/> of the Occident. send him the</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>next number when it comes out<lb/> (<date>February</date>) &amp;
                                        send me the 10 numbers I give<lb/> to Him. add his name to
                                        your List<lb/> of subscribers. I will collect their
                                        money<lb/> &amp; with what I trust soon to be<lb/> enabled
                                        to send you from the sale<lb/> of your Books I will add the
                                        amount<lb/> of those subscribers I have obtained<lb/> I
                                        shall obtain all the subscribers I<lb/> possibly can &amp;
                                        now Sir I must<lb/> come to a hasty conclusion<lb/> Pardon
                                        this scrawl my Business<lb/> occupying so much of my time
                                        gives<lb/> me but a few moments to private<lb/>
                                        correspondence</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Believe me to</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">remain your</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Sincere Well Wisher</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
